Service: zimbraAdmin

RenameDistributionList SOAP Command

Rename Distribution List
Access: domain admin sufficient

Authorization token required true
Admin Authorization token required true

RenameDistributionListRequest

    <RenameDistributionListRequest id="{value-of-zimbra-id}" newName="{new-DL-name}" /> ## RenameDistributionListRequest

The following table describes elements and attributes you can define within a <RenameDistributionListRequest> element:

XPath Required / Optional Description
@id Required (only 1) Type:String
Zimbra ID
@newName Required (only 1) Type:String
New Distribution List name

RenameDistributionListResponse

    <RenameDistributionListResponse> ## RenameDistributionListResponse
        <dl [dynamic="{dl-is-dynamic} (0|1)"] name="{name}" id="{id}"> ## DistributionListInfo
            (<dlm>{members} (String)</dlm>)*
            <owners>
                (<owner [type="{grantee-type} (usr|grp|egp|all|dom|gst|key|pub|email)"] id="{grantee-id}"
                            name="{grantee-name}" /> ## GranteeInfo)*
            </owners>
            (<a n="{key}" /> ## Attr)*
        </dl>
    </RenameDistributionListResponse>

The following table describes elements and attributes you can define within a <RenameDistributionListResponse> element:

XPath Required / Optional Description

Flags whether this is a dynamic distribution list or not

Name
/dl@id Required (only 1) Type:String
ID
/dl/dlm Optional (0 or more) Type:{members} (String)
dl-members
/dl/owners Required (only 1)
/dl/owners/owner Optional (0 or more)
/dl/owners/owner@type Optional (0 or 1) Type:usr|grp|egp|all|dom|gst|key|pub|email
Grantee type

Grantee ID
